@Node "GETPREFS" "dfa.guide/GETPREFS"
@Next "GETTEMPLATE"
@Prev "GETCURRENT"
@Toc "ArexxCommands"

The GETPREFS Command
....................

@{b}Syntax:@{ub}
     GETPREFS [SHOWAPPICON|APPICON] [AUTOSAVE|AS] [MAKEICON]
     [SECRETMODE|SM] [NETWORKMODE|NWMODE] [NETWORKRETRIES|NWRETRIES]
     [NETWORKDELAY|NWDELAY] [GROUPNAME1] [GROUPNAME2] [GROUPNAME3]
     [GROUPNAME4] [GROUPNAME5] [GROUPNAME6] [GROUPNAME7] [GROUPNAME8]
     [GROUPRELATION|GREL] [MODEMBAUD|MBAUD] [MODEMINIT|MINIT]
     [MODEMEXIT|MEXIT] [MODEMPREDIAL|MPDIAL] [MODEMSUFFDIAL|MSDIAL]
     [MODEMSERDEV|MDEV] [MODEMSERDEVNO|MDEVNO] [MODEMUSEODU|MODU]
     [MODEMRETRIES|MRETRIES] [MODEMDELAY|MDELAY]
     [PATHSADDRESSFILE|PAFILE] [PATHSEXTERNALDIR|PEXT]
     [PATHSASCIIED|PASCIIED] [PATHSASCIISHOW|PASCIISHOW] [SORTBY1]
     [SORTBY2] [SORTBY3] [SORTBY4] [VAR <name>] [STEM <name>]

@{b}Argument template:@{ub}
     SHOWAPPICON=APPICON/S, AUTOSAVE=AS/S, MAKEICON/S, SECRETMODE=SM/S,
     NETWORKMODE=NWMODE/S, NETWORKRETRIES=NWRETRIES/S,
     NETWORKDELAY=NWDELAY/S, GROUPNAME1/S, GROUPNAME2/S, GROUPNAME3/S,
     GROUPNAME4/S, GROUPNAME5/S, GROUPNAME6/S, GROUPNAME7/S,
     GROUPNAME8/S, GROUPRELATION=GREL/S, MODEMBAUD=MBAUD/S,
     MODEMINIT=MINIT/S, MODEMEXIT=MEXIT/S, MODEMPREDIAL=MPDIAL/S,
     MODEMSUFFDIAL=MSDIAL/S, MODEMSERDEV=MDEV/S,
     MODEMSERDEVNO=MDEVNO/K/S, MODEMUSEODU=MODU/S,
     MODEMRETRIES=MRETRIES/K/S, MODEMDELAY=MDELAY/S,
     PATHSADDRESSFILE=PAFILE/S, PATHSEXTERNALDIR=PEXT/S,
     PATHSASCIIED=PASCIIED/S, PATHSASCIISHOW=PASCIISHOW/S, SORTBY1/S,
     SORTBY2/S, SORTBY3/S, SORTBY4/S, VAR/K, STEM/K

@{b}Function:@{ub}
     Returns the settings of DFA. Only the first argument is used. The
     return value can be found in @{b}RESULT@{ub} or within the variable you can
     give together with the @{b}VAR@{ub} or @{b}STEM@{ub} keyword.

@{b}Argument description:@{ub}
        @{b}*@{ub} SHOWAPPICON|APPICON

          AppIcon:

             - 0 Show the AppIcon

             - 1 Don't show the AppIcon

        @{b}*@{ub} AUTOSAVE|AS

          Automatic saving of the address file.

             - ALWAYS Saves the address file as soon as you leave the
               @{b}DFA-Editors@{ub}.

             - REMOVE Thes the address file only, if you terminate the
               complete @{b}DFA@{ub} application.

             - ASK When you leave the @{b}DFA-Editor@{ub}, you're asked, if you
               wnat to save the address file.

        @{b}*@{ub} MAKEICON

          Generates an icon for the address files.

             - 0 Icon generation off

             - 1 Icon generation on

        @{b}*@{ub} SECRETMODE|SM

          Secret mode:

             - 0 Secret mode off

             - 1 Secret mode on

        @{b}*@{ub} NETWORKMODE|NWMODE

          Network mode:

             - 0 Network mode off

             - 1 Network mode on

        @{b}*@{ub} NETWORKRETRIES|NWRETRIES

          Number of retries, when @{b}DFA@{ub} tries to get write access to an
          address file.

        @{b}*@{ub} NETWORKDELAY|NWDELAY

          Number of seconds to wait between two retries.

        @{b}*@{ub} GROUPNAME1

        @{b}*@{ub} GROUPNAME2

        @{b}*@{ub} GROUPNAME3

        @{b}*@{ub} GROUPNAME4

        @{b}*@{ub} GROUPNAME5

        @{b}*@{ub} GROUPNAME6

        @{b}*@{ub} GROUPNAME7

        @{b}*@{ub} GROUPNAME8

          Name of the different groups.

        @{b}*@{ub} GROUPRELATION|GREL

          Group relation:

             - OR via @{b}OR@{ub}

             - AND via @{b}UND@{ub}.

        @{b}*@{ub} MODEMBAUD|MBAUD

          The baud rate of the modem. Possible values are:

             - 1200

             - 2400

             - 4800

             - 7200

             - 9600

             - 12000

             - 14400

             - 16800

             - 19200

             - 31250

             - 38400

             - 57600

             - 64000

             - 76800

             - 115000

        @{b}*@{ub} MODEMINIT|MINIT

          Init string.

        @{b}*@{ub} MODEMEXIT|MEXIT

          Exit string.

        @{b}*@{ub} MODEMPREDIAL|MPDIAL

          Predial string.

        @{b}*@{ub} MODEMSUFFDIAL|MSDIAL

          String, which is sent directly after the phone number.

        @{b}*@{ub} MODEMSERDEV|MDEV

          The name of the serial device.

        @{b}*@{ub} MODEMSERDEVNO|MDEVNO

          The number of the serial device.

        @{b}*@{ub} MODEMUSEODU|MODU

          Usage of the @{b}OwnDevUnit.library@{ub}:

             - 0 The @{b}OwnDevUnit.library@{ub} is not used.

             - 1 The @{b}OwnDevUnit.library@{ub} is used.

        @{b}*@{ub} MODEMRETRIES|MRETRIES

          Number of retries, if the line is busy.

        @{b}*@{ub} MODEMDELAY|MDELAY

          Delay (in seconds) between two retries.

        @{b}*@{ub} PATHSADDRESSFILE|PAFILE

          Path and name of the address file.

        @{b}*@{ub} PATHSEXTERNALDIR|PEXT

          Name of the drawer that contains the external files.

        @{b}*@{ub} PATHSASCIIED|PASCIIED

          Name (incl. path) of the text editor.

        @{b}*@{ub} PATHSASCIISHOW|PASCIISHOW

          Name (incl. path) of the text viewer.

        @{b}*@{ub} SORTBY1

        @{b}*@{ub} SORTBY2

        @{b}*@{ub} SORTBY3

        @{b}*@{ub} SORTBY4

          Each parameter can return one of the following keywords:

             - SALUTATION

             - FIRSTNAME

             - NAME

             - CO

             - STREET

             - ZIP

             - CITY

             - STATE

             - COUNTRY

             - BIRTHDAY

             - PHONE

             - FAX

             - EMAIL1

             - EMAIL2

             - EMAIL3

             - COMMENT

             - CLEAR Deleted sort criteria, i.e. none.

        @{b}*@{ub} VAR <name>

        @{b}*@{ub} STEM <name>

@{b}Results:@{ub}
     The return value depends on the argument you supply; see above.

@{b}Note:@{ub}
     -

@{b}Example:@{ub}
     -


@EndNode

